Description : This package consists of several python scripts, which can be used to perform flux calibration of uGMRT/GMRT phased-array observations of pulsar.
	      These scripts use the python wrapper of PSRCHIVE. It is mandatory to install PSRCHIVE with python wrapper to use these scripts.
	      These scripts also use 'gptool' for RFI flagging and bandshape estimator. 
	      This package allow user to perform several operations of raw uGMRT/GMRT data, based on user requirement. 
	      This is a semi-automated pipeline.

Required packages:

1) Install PSRCHIVE with python wrapper. See details at : http://psrchive.sourceforge.net/manuals/python/
2) Code is written in python 3.
3) Code uses GMRT pulsar tool (gptool).
4) For help and usage of any script type python script_name.py

Observations required:

1) At least one on and off scan on a standard flux calibrator source (e.g. 3C286,3C48 etc.)
2) At least one on and off scan on a nearby phase calibrator source.
3) Scan on pulsar

